  <text>
    <body>
      <div type="page" n="146">
        <pb n="146"/>
        <lg xml:id="block_A" xml:lang="he" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F057b76ce-b994-48fb-b262-10b58728149a.jp2/709,992,3121,767/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>שְׁמַע וּבִרְכוֹתֶיהָ</l>
          <l>SH&apos;MA UVIRCHOTEHA — SH&apos;MA AND ITS BLESSINGS</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:id="block_B" xml:lang="he" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F057b76ce-b994-48fb-b262-10b58728149a.jp2/2808,2000,1383,615/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>בָּרְכוּ אֶת יְיָ הַמְבֹרָךְ!</l>
          <l>בָּרוּךְ יְיָ הַמְבֹרָךְ</l>
          <l>לְעוֹלָם וָעֶד!</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:id="block_C" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F057b76ce-b994-48fb-b262-10b58728149a.jp2/469,1989,1336,595/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>BAR’CHU et Adonai hamvorach!</l>
          <l>Baruch Adonai ham&apos;vorach</l>
          <l>l&apos;olam va-ed!</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:id="block_D" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F057b76ce-b994-48fb-b262-10b58728149a.jp2/1204,2701,2219,552/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>PRAISE ADONAI to whom praise is due forever!</l>
          <l>Praised be Adonai to whom praise is due,</l>
          <l>now and forever!</l>
        </lg>
        <lg xml:id="block_E" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2F057b76ce-b994-48fb-b262-10b58728149a.jp2/433,5674,3695,741/max/0/default.jpg">
          <l>The Shma is one of the prayers one may recite in any language. M. Sotah 7:1</l>
          <l>For those who choose: The prayer leader at the word Bar&apos;chu (the call to worship) bends</l>
          <l>the knees and bows from the waist, and at » Adonai stands straight. »77 Baruch Adonai is the</l>
          <l>communal response, whereupon the community repeats the choreography of the first line.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
